## Builder ##

-> allows for the step-by-step creation of complex objects using the correct sequence of actions, The construction is
 controlled by a director object that only needs to know the type of object it is to create.

 -> The construction is controlled by a director object that only needs to know the type of object it is to create.

-> In normal practice, if we want to make a immutable User class, then we must pass all five information as parameters
 to constructor.
 Very good. Now what if only firstName and lastName are mandatory and rest 3 fields are optional.
 Problem !! We need more constructors.


 Examples:
 java.lang.StringBuilder#append()
 java.lang.StringBuffer#append()